cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.PL

This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it discusses memory caching in data-parallel frameworks such as Spark, Tez, and Storm. It may also belong to the Databases (cs.DB) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories as it deals with caching input and intermediate data in memory. The Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper proposes a new policy for cache management. Finally, the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category may also be relevant as the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed policy in Spark.
